23/05/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- On Thursday (22 May), Transport Minister Spartak Poci and his Macedonian counterpart, Milaim Ajdini, agreed on the final steps for completion of the railway link between the two countries. 
They also agreed that implementation is a priority.Poci said Albania must build the last 1.5km of the railway line and that additional funding must be secured beyond the $3m already raised for the project. 
In addition, the two officials discussed the regional Corridor 8 project and the expansion of fiber optic networks throughout both countries. 
(Zeri I Popullit - 23/05/03; ATA - 22/05/03)
